peopleAlsoAsk.question: How to identify fabric scissors?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet: Fabric scissors have blades with no serrations and a very sharp angle. They are sharper than paper scissors. If they are used to cut paper, they will become dull.

peopleAlsoAsk.question: How do you identify scissors?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet: A pair of scissors consists of a pair of blades pivoted so that the sharpened edges slide against each other when the handles (bows) opposite to the pivot are closed. Scissors are used for cutting various thin materials, such as paper, cardboard, metal foil, cloth, rope, and wire.

peopleAlsoAsk.question: Why are fabric scissors so expensive?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet: Craftsmanship: Many professional scissors are handcrafted by skilled artisans. The precision in manufacturing and attention to detail contribute to their higher cost. Design and Ergonomics: Well-designed scissors are ergonomically shaped to reduce strain on the hand during use.
